hello 2 0 2 3✨

Taking some time to reflect, reset & refocus so I can embrace all the blessings, growth & good things coming to me this new year. 

I’m taking a break & stepping away from socials for a bit— little detox. Can’t wait to catch up with you all when I’m back

Love & light 🤍

A lot can happen when you detox from social media & focus on yourself 🤍

Taking 3 weeks completely off socials was exactly what I needed to start the year off right. Here’s 5 things that happened:

- My productivity skyrocketed, I feel like I had so much more time in my day. I was much more active, more focused at work and 
had time for so many other things. I tried new restaurants, went to spin, barre and yoga, and read 3 books. 

- I took photos & videos to capture memories rather than creating content. It was refreshing to not have to worry about curating for the gram. I think maybe I’ll share more everyday moments.

- I was more present and intentional with my relationships. Social media is weird in that it connects us…. but can also isolate us. I took a good hard look at my parasocial relationships and chose to invest time with friends and family offline. It definitely strengthened those relationships that truly matter🫶🏼

- This is embarrassing but towards the end of 2022 my screentime was hovering around 13 hours per day. That’s so bad… each week it whittled down even more and now it’s under 4 hours 🙌🏼

- Oh and I moved! 📦

TLDR: it was a great 3 weeks 

#socialmediadetox #mentalhealth #lifelately #newhome #newbeginnings

Today marks 1 year with my new smile from @615smiledesignstudio 

We used 10 no prep veneers and 2 treatments of Restylane Kysse for a complete smile makeover. The veneers made my teeth more uniform and broadened my smile & we used Kysse to enhance my natural lips and define my cupids bow. The process was quick, pain free & since we used no-prep veneers we didn’t have to remove any tooth structure (no shark teeth here!) which was a non negotiable for me.

It’s been a great year with my new & improved smile 😁
